content:
A combination chart plots multiple sets of data on a single chart. Each set of data is based on a different field, making values easy to compare. You can also combine certain chart types to present data in different ways.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

User permissions needed: Enhanced Folder Sharing, Create and Customize Reports, and Report Builder.

With combination charts, you can:

* Add a line to an existing chart
* Add up to three columns or bars to a vertical column or horizontal bar chart
* Display different measures on the same chart

To add multiple measures on a chart in Lightning Experience:

1. Edit the chart for any report grouped by rows (summary report) or grouped by rows and columns (matrix report)
2. Verify that a summary measure is applied to each of the fields you want to plot on the Y axis
3. Add another measure by clicking + Measure and selecting the measure field to add

To add multiple measures on a chart in Salesforce Classic:

1. Edit the chart for any summary or matrix report, or edit a dashboard component that displays a summary or matrix report
2. Choose a chart type that allows combination charts (Bar, Column, Grouped column, Stacked column, Line, Cumulative line)
3. Select the Plot additional values checkbox and add up to three sets

When adding multiple measures to a chart, you can use different display options depending on your chart type. For columns or bars, click Add Bar or Add Column links to add up to three sets.

You can also use a separate axis for one of the added lines when using a vertical column chart.
title: Create Combination Charts in Salesforce
